247 static void MmwDemo_dssChirpIntHandler(uintptr_t arg)
248 {
249  MmwDemo_DSS_DataPathObj * dpObj = &gMmwDssMCB.dataPathObj[gMmwDssMCB.subFrameIndx];
250 
251  if((gMmwDssMCB.state == MmwDemo_DSS_STATE_STOPPED) ||
252  (gMmwDssMCB.dataPathContext.interFrameProcToken <= 0))
253  {
254  gMmwDssMCB.stats.chirpIntSkipCounter++;
255  return;
256  }
257 
258 #ifdef DBG
259  if (dpObj->chirpCount < NUM_CHIRP_TIME_STAMPS)
260  {
261  gChirpTimeStamp[dpObj->chirpCount] =
262  Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp();
263  }
264 #endif
265 
266  if (dpObj->chirpCount == 0)
267  {
268  MmwDemo_DSS_DataPathObj * dpObjPrev = dpObj;
269  uint8_t subFrameIndxPrev;
270  if (gMmwDssMCB.numSubFrames > 1)
271  {
272  if (gMmwDssMCB.subFrameIndx == 0)
273  {
274  subFrameIndxPrev = gMmwDssMCB.numSubFrames - 1;
275  }
276  else
277  {
278  subFrameIndxPrev = gMmwDssMCB.subFrameIndx - 1;
279  }
280  dpObjPrev = &gMmwDssMCB.dataPathObj[subFrameIndxPrev];
281  }
282 
283  /* Note: this is valid after the first frame */
284  dpObjPrev->timingInfo.interFrameProcessingEndMargin =
285  Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp() - dpObjPrev->timingInfo.interFrameProcessingEndTime -
286  dpObjPrev->timingInfo.subFrameSwitchingCycles;
287  }
288  else if (dpObj->chirpCount == dpObj->numChirpsPerChirpEvent)
289  {
290  dpObj->timingInfo.chirpProcessingEndMarginMin =
291  Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp() - dpObj->timingInfo.chirpProcessingEndTime;
292  dpObj->timingInfo.chirpProcessingEndMarginMax =
293  dpObj->timingInfo.chirpProcessingEndMarginMin;
294  }
295  else
296  {
297  uint32_t margin = Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp() - dpObj->timingInfo.chirpProcessingEndTime;
298  if (margin > dpObj->timingInfo.chirpProcessingEndMarginMax)
299  {
300  dpObj->timingInfo.chirpProcessingEndMarginMax = margin;
301  }
302  if (margin < dpObj->timingInfo.chirpProcessingEndMarginMin)
303  {
304  dpObj->timingInfo.chirpProcessingEndMarginMin = margin;
305  }
306  }
307  /* Increment interrupt counter for debugging purpose */
308  gMmwDssMCB.stats.chirpIntCounter++;
309 
310  /* Check if previous chirp processing has completed */
311  if (gMmwDssMCB.dataPathContext.chirpProcToken != 0)
312  {
313  MmwDemo_triggerDss2MssISR(MMWDEMO_DSS2MSS_CHIRP_PROC_DEADLINE_MISS_EXCEPTION);
314  DebugP_assert(0);
315  }
316 
317  gMmwDssMCB.dataPathContext.chirpProcToken++;
318 
319  /* Post event to notify chirp available interrupt */
320  Event_post(gMmwDssMCB.eventHandle, MMWDEMO_CHIRP_EVT);
321 }

332 {

376 static int32_t MmwDemo_dssMmwaveEventCallbackFxn(uint16_t msgId, uint16_t sbId, uint16_t sbLen, uint8_t *payload)
377 {
378  uint16_t asyncSB = RL_GET_SBID_FROM_UNIQ_SBID(sbId);
379 
380  /* Debug Message: */
381  /*System_printf ("Debug: MMWDemoDSS received BSS Event MsgId: %d [Sub Block Id: %d Sub Block Length: %d]\n",
382  msgId, sbId, sbLen); */
383 
384  /* Process the received message: */
385  switch (msgId)
386  {
387  case RL_RF_ASYNC_EVENT_MSG:
388  {
389  /* Received Asychronous Message: */
390  switch (asyncSB)
391  {
392  case RL_RF_AE_CPUFAULT_SB:
393  {
394  /* BSS fault */
395  MmwDemo_dssAssert(0);
396  break;
397  }
398  case RL_RF_AE_ESMFAULT_SB:
399  {
400  /* BSS fault */
401  MmwDemo_dssAssert(0);
402  break;
403  }
404  case RL_RF_AE_ANALOG_FAULT_SB:
405  {
406  /* Analog Fault */
407  MmwDemo_dssAssert(0);
408  break;
409  }
410  case RL_RF_AE_INITCALIBSTATUS_SB:
411  {
412  /* This event should be handled by mmwave internally, ignore the event here */
413  break;
414  }
415 
416  case RL_RF_AE_FRAME_TRIGGER_RDY_SB:
417  {
418  /* Post event to datapath task notify BSS events */
419  Event_post(gMmwDssMCB.eventHandle, MMWDEMO_BSS_FRAME_TRIGGER_READY_EVT);
420 
421  break;
422  }
423  case RL_RF_AE_MON_TIMING_FAIL_REPORT_SB:
424  {
425  /* Increment the statistics to reports that the calibration failed */
426  gMmwDssMCB.stats.numFailedTimingReports++;
427  break;
428  }
429  case RL_RF_AE_RUN_TIME_CALIB_REPORT_SB:
430  {
431  /* Increment the statistics to indicate that a calibration report was received */
432  gMmwDssMCB.stats.numCalibrationReports++;
433  break;
434  }
435  case RL_RF_AE_FRAME_END_SB:
436  {
437  gMmwDssMCB.stats.bssStopAsyncEvt++;
438  /*Received Frame Stop async event from BSS. Post event to datapath task.*/
439  Event_post(gMmwDssMCB.eventHandle, MMWDEMO_BSS_STOP_COMPLETE_EVT);
440  break;
441  }
442  default:
443  {
444  System_printf ("Error: Asynchronous Event SB Id %d not handled\n", asyncSB);
445  break;
446  }
447  }
448  break;
449  }
450  default:
451  {
452  System_printf ("Error: Asynchronous message %d is NOT handled\n", msgId);
453  break;
454  }
455  }
456  return 0;
457 }

580 static void MmwDemo_cfgUpdate(void *srcPtr, uint32_t offset, uint32_t size, int8_t subFrameNum)
581 {
582  /* if subFrameNum undefined, broadcast to all sub-frames */
583  if(subFrameNum == MMWDEMO_SUBFRAME_NUM_FRAME_LEVEL_CONFIG)
584  {
585  uint8_t indx;
586  for(indx = 0; indx < RL_MAX_SUBFRAMES; indx++)
587  {
588  memcpy((void *)((uint32_t) &gMmwDssMCB.cliCfg[indx] + offset), srcPtr, size);
589  }
590 
591  }
592  else
593  {
594  /* Apply configuration to specific subframe (or to position zero for the legacy case
595  where there is no advanced frame config) */
596  memcpy((void *)((uint32_t) &gMmwDssMCB.cliCfg[subFrameNum] + offset), srcPtr, size);
597  }

645 static void MmwDemo_mboxReadTask(UArg arg0, UArg arg1)
646 {
647  MmwDemo_message message;
648  int32_t retVal = 0;
649  int8_t subFrameNum;
650  uint32_t log2NumAvgChirpsTemp;
651 
652  /* wait for new message and process all the messsages received from the peer */
653  while(1)
654  {
655  Semaphore_pend(gMmwDssMCB.mboxSemHandle, BIOS_WAIT_FOREVER);
656 
657  /* Read the message from the peer mailbox: We are not trying to protect the read
658  * from the peer mailbox because this is only being invoked from a single thread */
659  retVal = Mailbox_read(gMmwDssMCB.peerMailbox, (uint8_t*)&message, sizeof(MmwDemo_message));
660  if (retVal < 0)
661  {
662  /* Error: Unable to read the message. Setup the error code and return values */
663  System_printf ("Error: Mailbox read failed [Error code %d]\n", retVal);
664  }
665  else if (retVal == 0)
666  {
667  /* We are done: There are no messages available from the peer execution domain. */
668  continue;
669  }
670  else
671  {
672  /* Flush out the contents of the mailbox to indicate that we are done with the message. This will
673  * allow us to receive another message in the mailbox while we process the received message. */
674  Mailbox_readFlush (gMmwDssMCB.peerMailbox);
675 
676  /* Process the received message: */
677  subFrameNum = message.subFrameNum;
678 
679  switch (message.type)
680  {
681  case MMWDEMO_MSS2DSS_GUIMON_CFG:
682  {
683  /* Save guimon configuration */
684  MmwDemo_cfgUpdate((void *)&message.body.guiMonSel,
685  offsetof(MmwDemo_CliCfg_t, guiMonSel),
686  sizeof(MmwDemo_GuiMonSel), subFrameNum);
687  break;
688  }
689  case MMWDEMO_MSS2DSS_CFAR_RANGE_CFG:
690  {
691  MmwDemo_cfgUpdate((void *)&message.body.cfarCfg,
692  offsetof(MmwDemo_CliCfg_t, cfarCfgRange),
693  sizeof(MmwDemo_CfarCfg), subFrameNum);
694  break;
695  }
696  case MMWDEMO_MSS2DSS_CFAR_DOPPLER_CFG:
697  {
698  /* Save cfarDoppler configuration */
699  MmwDemo_cfgUpdate((void *)&message.body.cfarCfg,
700  offsetof(MmwDemo_CliCfg_t, cfarCfgDoppler),
701  sizeof(MmwDemo_CfarCfg), subFrameNum);
702 
703  break;
704  }
705  case MMWDEMO_MSS2DSS_PEAK_GROUPING_CFG:
706  {
707  /* Save Peak grouping configuration */
708  MmwDemo_cfgUpdate((void *)&message.body.peakGroupingCfg,
709  offsetof(MmwDemo_CliCfg_t, peakGroupingCfg),
710  sizeof(MmwDemo_PeakGroupingCfg), subFrameNum);
711  break;
712  }
713  case MMWDEMO_MSS2DSS_MULTI_OBJ_BEAM_FORM:
714  {
715  /* Save multi object beam forming configuration */
716  MmwDemo_cfgUpdate((void*)&message.body.multiObjBeamFormingCfg,
717  offsetof(MmwDemo_CliCfg_t, multiObjBeamFormingCfg),
718  sizeof(MmwDemo_MultiObjBeamFormingCfg),
719  subFrameNum);
720  break;
721  }
722  case MMWDEMO_MSS2DSS_CALIB_DC_RANGE_SIG:
723  {
724  /* Save of DC range antenna signature configuration */
725  MmwDemo_cfgUpdate((void *)&message.body.calibDcRangeSigCfg,
726  offsetof(MmwDemo_CliCfg_t, calibDcRangeSigCfg),
727  sizeof(MmwDemo_CalibDcRangeSigCfg), subFrameNum);
728 
729  log2NumAvgChirpsTemp = MmwDemo_floorLog2(message.body.calibDcRangeSigCfg.numAvgChirps);
730  /* Save log2NumAvgChirps */
731  if (subFrameNum == MMWDEMO_SUBFRAME_NUM_FRAME_LEVEL_CONFIG)
732  {
733  uint8_t indx;
734  for(indx = 0; indx < RL_MAX_SUBFRAMES; indx++)
735  {

1010  {
1011  retVal = -1;
1012  goto Exit;
1013  }
1014  memcpy(&ptrCurrBuffer[sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_dataObjDescr)], (void *)obj->detObj2D, itemPayloadLen);
1015 
1016  message.body.detObj.tlv[tlvIdx].length = itemPayloadLen + sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_dataObjDescr);
1017  message.body.detObj.tlv[tlvIdx].type = MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_DETECTED_POINTS;
1018  message.body.detObj.tlv[tlvIdx].address = (uint32_t) ptrCurrBuffer;
1019  tlvIdx++;
1020 
1021  /* Incrementing pointer to HSM buffer */
1022  ptrCurrBuffer += itemPayloadLen + sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_dataObjDescr);
1023  totalPacketLen += sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl) + itemPayloadLen + sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_dataObjDescr);
1024  }
1025 
1026  /* Sending range profile: 2bytes * numRangeBins */
1027  if (pGuiMonSel->logMagRange == 1)
1028  {

1033  retVal = -1;

1038  for(i = 0; i < obj->numRangeBins; i++)

1040  ptrMatrix[i] = obj->detMatrix[i*obj->numDopplerBins];
1041  }
1042 
1043  message.body.detObj.tlv[tlvIdx].length = itemPayloadLen;
1044  message.body.detObj.tlv[tlvIdx].type = MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_RANGE_PROFILE;
1045  message.body.detObj.tlv[tlvIdx].address = (uint32_t) ptrCurrBuffer;
1046  tlvIdx++;
1047 
1048  /* Incrementing pointer to HSM buffer */
1049  ptrCurrBuffer = (uint8_t *)((uint32_t)ptrHsmBuffer + totalHsmSize);
1050  totalPacketLen += sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl) + itemPayloadLen;
1051  }
1052 
1053  /* Sending range profile: 2bytes * numRangeBins */
1054  if (pGuiMonSel->noiseProfile == 1)
1055  {
1056  uint32_t maxDopIdx = obj->numDopplerBins/2 -1;
1057  itemPayloadLen = sizeof(uint16_t) * obj->numRangeBins;
1058  totalHsmSize += itemPayloadLen;
1059  if(totalHsmSize > outputBufSize)
1060  {
1061  retVal = -1;
1062  goto Exit;
1063  }
1064 
1065  uint16_t *ptrMatrix = (uint16_t *)ptrCurrBuffer;
1066  for(i = 0; i < obj->numRangeBins; i++)

1068  ptrMatrix[i] = obj->detMatrix[i*obj->numDopplerBins + maxDopIdx];
1069  }
1070 
1071  message.body.detObj.tlv[tlvIdx].length = itemPayloadLen;
1072  message.body.detObj.tlv[tlvIdx].type = MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_NOISE_PROFILE;
1073  message.body.detObj.tlv[tlvIdx].address = (uint32_t) ptrCurrBuffer;
1074  tlvIdx++;
1075 
1076  /* Incrementing pointer to HSM buffer */
1077  ptrCurrBuffer = (uint8_t *)((uint32_t)ptrHsmBuffer + totalHsmSize);
1078  totalPacketLen += sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl) + itemPayloadLen;
1079  }
1080 
1081  /* Sending range Azimuth Heat Map */
1082  if (pGuiMonSel->rangeAzimuthHeatMap == 1)
1083  {
1084  itemPayloadLen = obj->numRangeBins * obj->numVirtualAntAzim * sizeof(cmplx16ImRe_t);
1085  message.body.detObj.tlv[tlvIdx].length = itemPayloadLen;
1086  message.body.detObj.tlv[tlvIdx].type = MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_AZIMUT_STATIC_HEAT_MAP;
1087  message.body.detObj.tlv[tlvIdx].address = (uint32_t) obj->azimuthStaticHeatMap;
1088  tlvIdx++;
1089 
1090  totalPacketLen += sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl) + itemPayloadLen;
1091  }
1092 
1093 
1094  /* Sending range Doppler Heat Map */
1095  if (pGuiMonSel->rangeDopplerHeatMap == 1)
1096  {
1097  itemPayloadLen = obj->numRangeBins * obj->numDopplerBins * sizeof(uint16_t);
1098  message.body.detObj.tlv[tlvIdx].length = itemPayloadLen;
1099  message.body.detObj.tlv[tlvIdx].type = MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_RANGE_DOPPLER_HEAT_MAP;
1100  message.body.detObj.tlv[tlvIdx].address = (uint32_t) obj->detMatrix;
1101  tlvIdx++;
1102 
1103  totalPacketLen += sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl) + itemPayloadLen;
1104  }
1105 
1106  /* Sending stats information */
1107  if (pGuiMonSel->statsInfo == 1)
1108  {
1109  MmwDemo_output_message_stats stats;
1110  itemPayloadLen = sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_stats);
1111  totalHsmSize += itemPayloadLen;
1112  if(totalHsmSize > outputBufSize)
1113  {
1114  retVal = -1;
1115  goto Exit;
1116  }
1117 
1118  stats.interChirpProcessingMargin = (uint32_t) (obj->timingInfo.chirpProcessingEndMarginMin/DSP_CLOCK_MHZ);
1119  stats.interFrameProcessingMargin = (uint32_t) (obj->timingInfo.interFrameProcessingEndMargin/DSP_CLOCK_MHZ);
1120  stats.interFrameProcessingTime = (uint32_t) (obj->timingInfo.interFrameProcCycles/DSP_CLOCK_MHZ);
1121  stats.transmitOutputTime = (uint32_t) (obj->timingInfo.transmitOutputCycles/DSP_CLOCK_MHZ);
1122  stats.activeFrameCPULoad = obj->timingInfo.activeFrameCPULoad;
1123  stats.interFrameCPULoad = obj->timingInfo.interFrameCPULoad;
1124  memcpy(ptrCurrBuffer, (void *)&stats, itemPayloadLen);
1125 
1126  message.body.detObj.tlv[tlvIdx].length = itemPayloadLen;
1127  message.body.detObj.tlv[tlvIdx].type = MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_STATS;
1128  message.body.detObj.tlv[tlvIdx].address = (uint32_t) ptrCurrBuffer;;
1129  tlvIdx++;
1130 
1131  /* Incrementing pointer to HSM buffer */
1132  ptrCurrBuffer = (uint8_t *)((uint32_t)ptrHsmBuffer + totalHsmSize);
1133  totalPacketLen += sizeof(MmwDemo_output_message_tl) + itemPayloadLen;
1134  }
1135 
1136  if( retVal == 0)
1137  {
1138  message.body.detObj.header.numTLVs = tlvIdx;
1139  /* Round up packet length to multiple of MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_SEGMENT_LEN */
1140  message.body.detObj.header.totalPacketLen = MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_SEGMENT_LEN *
1141  ((totalPacketLen + (MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_SEGMENT_LEN-1))/MMWDEMO_OUTPUT_MSG_SEGMENT_LEN);
1142  message.body.detObj.header.timeCpuCycles = Cycleprofiler_getTimeStamp();
1143  message.body.detObj.header.frameNumber = gMmwDssMCB.stats.frameStartIntCounter;
1144  message.body.detObj.header.subFrameNumber = gMmwDssMCB.subFrameIndx;
1145  if (MmwDemo_mboxWrite(&message) != 0)
1146  {
1147  retVal = -1;
1148  }
1149  }
1150 Exit:
1151  return retVal;
1152 }

1183 void MmwDemo_dssDataPathOutputLogging(MmwDemo_DSS_DataPathObj * dataPathObj)
1184 {
1185  int32_t errCode;
1186 
1187  /* Sending detected objects to logging buffer and shipped out from MSS UART */
1188  if (gMmwDssMCB.loggingBufferAvailable == 1)
1189  {
1190  /* Set the logging buffer available flag to be 0 */
1191  gMmwDssMCB.loggingBufferAvailable = 0;
1192 
1193  /*If LVDS user data streaming is enabled for this subframe, send user data through LVDS as well.*/
1194  if(dataPathObj->cliCfg->lvdsStreamCfg.isSwEnabled != 0)
1195  {
1196  /* Delete previous SW session if it exists. SW session is being
1197  reconfigured every frame/subframe because number of detected objects
1198  may change every frame/subframe which implies that the size of
1199  the streamed data may change. */
1200  if(gMmwDssMCB.lvdsStream.swSessionHandle != NULL)
1201  {
1202  MmwDemo_LVDSStreamDeleteSwSession(gMmwDssMCB.lvdsStream.swSessionHandle);
1203  }

1205  if (MmwDemo_LVDSStreamSwConfig(dataPathObj) < 0)
1206  {
1207  System_printf("Failed LVDS stream SW configuration\n");
1208  return;
1209  }

1211  gMmwDssMCB.lvdsStream.userDataHeader.frameNum = gMmwDssMCB.stats.frameStartEvt;
1212  gMmwDssMCB.lvdsStream.userDataHeader.detObjNum = dataPathObj->numDetObj;
1213  gMmwDssMCB.lvdsStream.userDataHeader.reserved = 0xABCD;
1214 
1215  /* If SW LVDS stream is enabled, start the session here. User data will imediatelly
1216  start to stream over LVDS.*/
1217  if(CBUFF_activateSession (gMmwDssMCB.lvdsStream.swSessionHandle, &errCode) < 0)
1218  {
1219  System_printf("Failed to activate CBUFF session for LVDS stream SW. errCode=%d\n",errCode);
1220  return;
1221  }
1222  }
1223 
1224  /* Save output in logging buffer - HSRAM memory and a message is sent to MSS to notify
1225  logging buffer is ready */
1226  if (MmwDemo_dssSendProcessOutputToMSS((uint8_t *)&gHSRAM.dataPathDetectionPayload[0],
1227  (uint32_t)MMW_DATAPATH_DET_PAYLOAD_SIZE,
1228  dataPathObj) < 0)
1229  {
1230  /* Increment logging error */
1231  gMmwDssMCB.stats.detObjLoggingErr++;
1232  }
1233 
1234  }
1235  else
1236  {
1237  /* Logging buffer is not available, skip saving detected objects to logging buffer */
1238  gMmwDssMCB.stats.detObjLoggingSkip++;
1239  }
1240 }

1738 bool MmwDemo_parseProfileAndChirpConfig(MmwDemo_DSS_DataPathObj *dataPathObj,
1739  MMWave_CtrlCfg* ptrCtrlCfg, uint8_t subFrameIndx)
1740 {
1741  uint16_t frameChirpStartIdx;
1742  uint16_t frameChirpEndIdx;
1743  uint16_t numLoops;
1744  int16_t frameTotalChirps;
1745  int32_t errCode;
1746  uint32_t profileLoopIdx, chirpLoopIdx;
1747  bool foundValidProfile = false;
1748  uint16_t channelTxEn;
1749  uint8_t channel;
1750  uint8_t numRxChannels = 0;
1751  MMWave_OpenCfg* ptrOpenCfg;
1752  uint8_t rxAntOrder [SYS_COMMON_NUM_RX_CHANNEL];
1753  uint8_t txAntOrder [SYS_COMMON_NUM_TX_ANTENNAS];
1754  int32_t i;
1755  int32_t txIdx, rxIdx;
1756 
1757  /* Get data path object and control configuration */
1758  ptrOpenCfg = &gMmwDssMCB.cfg.openCfg;
1759 
1760  /* Get the Transmit channel enable mask: */
1761  channelTxEn = ptrOpenCfg->chCfg.txChannelEn;
1762 
1763  /* Find total number of Rx Channels */
1764  for (channel = 0; channel < SYS_COMMON_NUM_RX_CHANNEL; channel++)
1765  {
1766  rxAntOrder[channel] = 0;
1767  if(ptrOpenCfg->chCfg.rxChannelEn & (0x1U << channel))
1768  {
1769  rxAntOrder[numRxChannels] = channel;
1770  /* Track the number of receive channels: */
1771  numRxChannels += 1;
1772  }
1773  }
1774  dataPathObj->numRxAntennas = numRxChannels;
1775 
1776  if (ptrCtrlCfg->dfeDataOutputMode == MMWave_DFEDataOutputMode_ADVANCED_FRAME)
1777  {
1778  MmwDemo_dssAssert(
1779  ptrCtrlCfg->u.advancedFrameCfg.frameCfg.frameSeq.subFrameCfg[subFrameIndx].numOfBurst == 1);
1780  }
1781 
1782  /* read frameCfg chirp start/stop*/
1783  frameChirpStartIdx = MmwDemo_getChirpStartIdx(ptrCtrlCfg, subFrameIndx);
1784  frameChirpEndIdx = MmwDemo_getChirpEndIdx(ptrCtrlCfg, subFrameIndx);
1785  numLoops = MmwDemo_getNumLoops(ptrCtrlCfg, subFrameIndx);
1786 
1787  frameTotalChirps = frameChirpEndIdx - frameChirpStartIdx + 1;
1788 
1789  /* since validChirpTxEnBits is static array of 32 */
1790  MmwDemo_dssAssert(frameTotalChirps <= 32);
1791 
1792  /* loop for profiles and find if it has valid chirps */
1793  /* we support only one profile in this processing chain */
1794  for (profileLoopIdx = 0;
1795  ((profileLoopIdx < MMWAVE_MAX_PROFILE) && (foundValidProfile == false));
1796  profileLoopIdx++)
1797  {
1798  uint32_t mmWaveNumChirps = 0;
1799  bool validProfileHasOneTxPerChirp = false;
1800  bool validChirpHasOneTxPerChirp = false;
1801  uint16_t validProfileTxEn = 0;
1802  uint16_t validChirpTxEnBits[32] = {0};
1803  MMWave_ProfileHandle profileHandle;
1804 
1805  profileHandle = MmwDemo_getProfileHandle(ptrCtrlCfg, profileLoopIdx);
1806  if (profileHandle == NULL)
1807  continue; /* skip this profile */
1808 
1809  /* get numChirps for this profile; skip error checking */
1810  MMWave_getNumChirps(profileHandle, &mmWaveNumChirps, &errCode);
1811  /* loop for chirps and find if it has valid chirps for the frame
1812  looping around for all chirps in a profile, in case
1813  there are duplicate chirps
1814  */
1815  for (chirpLoopIdx = 1; chirpLoopIdx <= mmWaveNumChirps; chirpLoopIdx++)
1816  {
1817  MMWave_ChirpHandle chirpHandle;
1818  /* get handle and read ChirpCfg */
1819  if (MMWave_getChirpHandle(profileHandle, chirpLoopIdx, &chirpHandle, &errCode)==0)
1820  {
1821  rlChirpCfg_t chirpCfg;
1822  if (MMWave_getChirpCfg(chirpHandle, &chirpCfg, &errCode)==0)
1823  {
1824  uint16_t chirpTxEn = chirpCfg.txEnable;
1825  /* do chirps fall in range and has valid antenna enabled */
1826  if ((chirpCfg.chirpStartIdx >= frameChirpStartIdx) &&
1827  (chirpCfg.chirpEndIdx <= frameChirpEndIdx) &&
1828  ((chirpTxEn & channelTxEn) > 0))
1829  {
1830  uint16_t idx = 0;
1831  for (idx = (chirpCfg.chirpStartIdx - frameChirpStartIdx);
1832  idx <= (chirpCfg.chirpEndIdx - frameChirpStartIdx); idx++)
1833  {
1834  validChirpTxEnBits[idx] = chirpTxEn;
1835  foundValidProfile = true;
1836  }
1837 
1838  }
1839  }
1840  }
1841  }
1842  /* now loop through unique chirps and check if we found all of the ones
1843  needed for the frame and then determine the azimuth antenna
1844  configuration
1845  */
1846  if (foundValidProfile) {
1847  for (chirpLoopIdx = 0; chirpLoopIdx < frameTotalChirps; chirpLoopIdx++)
1848  {
1849  uint16_t chirpTxEn = validChirpTxEnBits[chirpLoopIdx];
1850  validChirpHasOneTxPerChirp = false;
1851  if (chirpTxEn == 0) {
1852  /* this profile doesnt have all the needed chirps */
1853  foundValidProfile = false;
1854  break;
1855  }
1856 
1857  if(dataPathObj->cliCfg->bpmCfg.isEnabled)
1858  {
1859  /*For configuration purposes, BPM should be treated as if it was TDM with 2 TX antennas
1860  and one TX per chirp. This way, all logic below will follow through for BPM.
1861  Just need to check here if all TX antennas are enabled for BPM.*/
1862  validChirpHasOneTxPerChirp = true;
1863  /* In case of BPM check if both TX antennas are enabled*/
1864  if(chirpTxEn != 0x3)
1865  {
1866  /* This frame is configured as BPM but this chirp does not enable both TX antennas*/
1867  foundValidProfile = false;
1868  System_printf("Bad BPM configuration. chirpTxEn=%d for chirp %d \n",chirpTxEn,chirpLoopIdx);
1869  break;
1870  }
1871  }
1872  else
1873  {
1874  validChirpHasOneTxPerChirp = ((chirpTxEn == 0x1) || (chirpTxEn == 0x2));
1875  }
1876  /* if this is the first chirp, record the chirp's
1877  MIMO config as profile's MIMO config. We dont handle intermix
1878  at this point */
1879  if (chirpLoopIdx==0) {
1880  validProfileHasOneTxPerChirp = validChirpHasOneTxPerChirp;
1881  }
1882  /* check the chirp's MIMO config against Profile's MIMO config */
1883  if (validChirpHasOneTxPerChirp != validProfileHasOneTxPerChirp)
1884  {
1885  /* this profile doesnt have all chirps with same MIMO config */
1886  foundValidProfile = false;
1887  break;
1888  }
1889  /* save the antennas actually enabled in this profile */
1890  validProfileTxEn |= chirpTxEn;
1891  }
1892  }
1893 
1894  /* found valid chirps for the frame; mark this profile valid */
1895  if (foundValidProfile == true) {
1896  rlProfileCfg_t profileCfg;
1897  uint32_t numTxAntAzim = 0;
1898  uint32_t numTxAntElev = 0;
1899  rlProfileCfg_t ptrProfileCfg;
1900 
1901  /* Get profile id from profile config */
1902  if(MMWave_getProfileCfg(profileHandle, &ptrProfileCfg, &errCode) < 0)
1903  {
1904  MmwDemo_dssAssert(0);
1905  }
1906  dataPathObj->validProfileIdx = ptrProfileCfg.profileId;
1907 
1908  dataPathObj->numTxAntennas = 0;
1909  if (!validProfileHasOneTxPerChirp)
1910  {
1911  numTxAntAzim=1;
1912  }
1913  else
1914  {
1915  if (validProfileTxEn & 0x1)
1916  {
1917  numTxAntAzim++;
1918  }
1919  if (validProfileTxEn & 0x2)
1920  {
1921  numTxAntAzim++;
1922  }
1923  }
1924  //System_printf("Azimuth Tx: %d (MIMO:%d) \n",numTxAntAzim,validProfileHasMIMO);
1925  dataPathObj->numTxAntennas = numTxAntAzim + numTxAntElev;
1926  dataPathObj->numVirtualAntAzim = numTxAntAzim * dataPathObj->numRxAntennas;
1927  dataPathObj->numVirtualAntElev = numTxAntElev * dataPathObj->numRxAntennas;
1928  dataPathObj->numVirtualAntennas = dataPathObj->numVirtualAntAzim + dataPathObj->numVirtualAntElev;
1929 
1930  /* Sanity Check: Ensure that the number of antennas is within system limits */
1931  MmwDemo_dssAssert (dataPathObj->numVirtualAntennas > 0);
1932  MmwDemo_dssAssert (dataPathObj->numVirtualAntennas <= (SYS_COMMON_NUM_TX_ANTENNAS * SYS_COMMON_NUM_RX_CHANNEL));
1933 
1934  /* Copy the Rx channel compensation coefficients from common area to data path structure */
1935  if (validProfileHasOneTxPerChirp)
1936  {
1937  for (i = 0; i < dataPathObj->numTxAntennas; i++)
1938  {
1939  if(dataPathObj->cliCfg->bpmCfg.isEnabled)
1940  {
1941  /*If BPM is enabled, need to assume order of the antennas as it can not
1942  be derived from the chirp/profile configuration because both TX antennas
1943  are enabled in both chirps. Will assume that the order is 0,1,...[numTxAntennas-1]*/
1944  txAntOrder[i] = i;
1945  }
1946  else
1947  {
1948  txAntOrder[i] = MmwDemo_floorLog2(validChirpTxEnBits[i]);
1949  }
1950  }
1951  for (txIdx = 0; txIdx < dataPathObj->numTxAntennas; txIdx++)
1952  {
1953  for (rxIdx = 0; rxIdx < dataPathObj->numRxAntennas; rxIdx++)
1954  {
1955  dataPathObj->compRxChanCfg.rxChPhaseComp[txIdx*dataPathObj->numRxAntennas + rxIdx] =
1956  dataPathObj->cliCommonCfg->compRxChanCfg.rxChPhaseComp[txAntOrder[txIdx]*SYS_COMMON_NUM_RX_CHANNEL + rxAntOrder[rxIdx]];
1957 
1958  }
1959 
1960  }
1961  }
1962  else
1963  {
1964  cmplx16ImRe_t one;
1965  one.imag = 0;
1966  one.real = 0x7fff;
1967  for (txIdx = 0; txIdx < dataPathObj->numTxAntennas; txIdx++)
1968  {
1969  for (rxIdx = 0; rxIdx < dataPathObj->numRxAntennas; rxIdx++)
1970  {
1971  dataPathObj->compRxChanCfg.rxChPhaseComp[txIdx*dataPathObj->numRxAntennas + rxIdx] = one;
1972  }
1973 
1974  }
1975  }
1976  /* Get the profile configuration: */
1977  if (MMWave_getProfileCfg (profileHandle, &profileCfg, &errCode) < 0)
1978  {
1979  System_printf ("Error: Unable to get the profile configuration [Error code %d]\n", errCode);
1980  MmwDemo_dssAssert (0);
1981  return -1;
1982  }
1983 
1984  /* multiplicity of 4 due to windowing library function requirement */
1985  if ((profileCfg.numAdcSamples % 4) != 0)
1986  {
1987  System_printf("Number of ADC samples must be multiple of 4\n");
1988  MmwDemo_dssAssert(0);
1989  }
1990  dataPathObj->numAdcSamples = profileCfg.numAdcSamples;
1991  dataPathObj->numRangeBins = MmwDemo_pow2roundup(dataPathObj->numAdcSamples);
1992  dataPathObj->numChirpsPerFrame = (frameChirpEndIdx -frameChirpStartIdx + 1) *
1993  numLoops;
1994  dataPathObj->numAngleBins = MMW_NUM_ANGLE_BINS;
1995  dataPathObj->numDopplerBins = dataPathObj->numChirpsPerFrame/dataPathObj->numTxAntennas;
1996 
1997  /* Multiplicity of 4 due to windowing library function requirement.
1998  Minimum size of 16 due to DSPLib restriction - FFT size must be bigger than 16.*/
1999  if (((dataPathObj->numDopplerBins % 4) != 0) ||
2000  (dataPathObj->numDopplerBins < 16))
2001  {
2002  System_printf("Number of Doppler bins must be at least 16 and it must be a multiple of 4.\n");
2003  MmwDemo_dssAssert(0);
2004  }
2005 
2006  if (dataPathObj->cliCfg->extendedMaxVelocityCfg.enabled &&
2007  dataPathObj->cliCfg->multiObjBeamFormingCfg.enabled)
2008  {
2009  System_printf("Simultaneous multi object beam forming and extended maximum velocity is not supported.\n");
2010  MmwDemo_dssAssert(0);
2011  }
2012 
2013  if (dataPathObj->cliCfg->extendedMaxVelocityCfg.enabled && numTxAntAzim == 1)
2014  {
2015  System_printf("Extended maximum velocity technique is supported only in TDM MIMO\n");
2016  MmwDemo_dssAssert(0);
2017  }
2018 
2019 #ifndef MMW_ENABLE_NEGATIVE_FREQ_SLOPE
2020  /* Check frequency slope */
2021  if (profileCfg.freqSlopeConst < 0)
2022  {
2023  System_printf("Frequency slope must be positive\n");
2024  MmwDemo_dssAssert(0);
2025  }
2026 #endif
2027  dataPathObj->rangeResolution = MMWDEMO_SPEED_OF_LIGHT_IN_METERS_PER_SEC *
2028  profileCfg.digOutSampleRate * 1e3 /
2029  (2 * profileCfg.freqSlopeConst * ((3.6*1e3*900) /
2030  (1U << 26)) * 1e12 * dataPathObj->numRangeBins);
2031  dataPathObj->xyzOutputQFormat = (uint8_t) ceil(log10(16. /
2032  fabs(dataPathObj->rangeResolution))/log10(2));
2033  }
2034  }
2035  return foundValidProfile;

2044 void MmwDemo_parseAdcBufCfg(MmwDemo_DSS_DataPathObj *dataPathObj)
2045 {
2046  uint8_t numBytePerSample = 0;
2047  uint32_t chirpThreshold;
2048  uint32_t maxChirpThreshold;
2049  uint32_t bytesPerChirp;
2050  MmwDemo_ADCBufCfg *adcBufCfg = &dataPathObj->cliCfg->adcBufCfg;
2051 
2052  /* Check if ADC configuration is supported:*/
2053  /* ADC out bits: must be 16 Bits */
2054  MmwDemo_dssAssert(dataPathObj->cfg->openCfg.adcOutCfg.fmt.b2AdcBits == 2);
2055 
2056  /* ADC data format: must be complex */
2057  /*adcCfg command*/
2058  if((dataPathObj->cfg->openCfg.adcOutCfg.fmt.b2AdcOutFmt != 1) &&
2059  (dataPathObj->cfg->openCfg.adcOutCfg.fmt.b2AdcOutFmt != 2))
2060  {
2061  MmwDemo_dssAssert(0);
2062  }
2063  /*adcbufCfg command*/
2064  MmwDemo_dssAssert(adcBufCfg->adcFmt == 0);
2065 
2066  /* ADC channel interleave mode: must be non-interleaved */
2067  MmwDemo_dssAssert(adcBufCfg->chInterleave == 1);
2068 
2069  /* Complex dataFormat has 4 bytes */
2070  numBytePerSample = 4;
2071 
2072  /* calculate max possible chirp threshold */
2073  bytesPerChirp = dataPathObj->numAdcSamples * dataPathObj->numRxAntennas * numBytePerSample;
2074 
2075  /* find maximum number of full chirps that can fit in the ADCBUF memory, while
2076  also being able to divide numChirpsPerFrame, we do not want remainder processing */
2077  maxChirpThreshold = SOC_XWR16XX_DSS_ADCBUF_SIZE / bytesPerChirp;
2078 
2079  /* There is a maximum of 8 CPs and CQs, so lets limit maxChirpThreshold to be that*/
2080  if(maxChirpThreshold > SYS_COMMON_CQ_MAX_CHIRP_THRESHOLD)
2081  {
2082  maxChirpThreshold = SYS_COMMON_CQ_MAX_CHIRP_THRESHOLD;
2083  }
2084 
2085  if (maxChirpThreshold >= dataPathObj->numChirpsPerFrame)
2086  {
2087  maxChirpThreshold = dataPathObj->numChirpsPerFrame;
2088  }
2089  else
2090  {
2091  /* find largest divisor of numChirpsPerFrame no bigger than maxChirpThreshold */
2092  while (dataPathObj->numChirpsPerFrame % maxChirpThreshold)
2093  {
2094  maxChirpThreshold--;
2095  }
2096  }
2097 
2098  /* ADCBuf control function requires argument alignment at 4 bytes boundary */
2099  chirpThreshold = adcBufCfg->chirpThreshold;
2100 
2101  /* if automatic, set to the calculated max */
2102  if (chirpThreshold == 0)
2103  {
2104  chirpThreshold = maxChirpThreshold;
2105  }
2106  else
2107  {
2108  if (chirpThreshold > maxChirpThreshold)
2109  {
2110  System_printf("Desired chirpThreshold %d higher than max possible of %d, setting to max\n",
2111  chirpThreshold, maxChirpThreshold);
2112  chirpThreshold = maxChirpThreshold;
2113  }
2114  else
2115  {
2116  /* check for divisibility of the user provided threshold */
2117  MmwDemo_dssAssert((dataPathObj->numChirpsPerFrame % chirpThreshold) == 0);
2118  }
2119  }
2120 
2121  /* Save info in data path Object */
2122  dataPathObj->numChirpsPerChirpEvent = chirpThreshold;
2123  dataPathObj->numBytePerSample = numBytePerSample;
2124 }

2684

2687  *****************************************************************************/

2689  Semaphore_Params_init(&semParams);

2695

2697  mboxCfg.chType = MAILBOX_CHTYPE_MULTI;
2698  mboxCfg.chId = MAILBOX_CH_ID_0;
2699  mboxCfg.writeMode = MAILBOX_MODE_BLOCKING;
2700  mboxCfg.readMode = MAILBOX_MODE_CALLBACK;
2701  mboxCfg.readCallback = &MmwDemo_mboxCallback;
2702 
2703  gMmwDssMCB.peerMailbox = Mailbox_open(MAILBOX_TYPE_MSS, &mboxCfg, &errCode);
2704  if (gMmwDssMCB.peerMailbox == NULL)
2705  {
2706  /* Error: Unable to open the mailbox */
2707  System_printf("Error: Unable to open the Mailbox to the DSS [Error code %d]\n", errCode);
2708  return;
2709  }
2710 
2711  /* Debug Message: */
2712  System_printf("Debug: DSS Mailbox Handle %p\n", gMmwDssMCB.peerMailbox);
2713 
2714  /* Create task to handle mailbox messges */
2715  Task_Params_init(&taskParams);
2716  Task_create(MmwDemo_mboxReadTask, &taskParams, NULL);
2717

2719  if ((errCode = MmwDemo_LVDSStreamInit()) < 0 )
2720  {

2722  return;
2723  }
2724

2726  * Create Event to handle mmwave callback and system datapath events
2727  *****************************************************************************/
2728  /* Default instance configuration params */
2729  Error_init(&eb);
2730  gMmwDssMCB.eventHandle = Event_create(NULL, &eb);
2731  if (gMmwDssMCB.eventHandle == NULL)
2732  {
2733  /* FATAL_TBA */
2734  System_printf("Error: MMWDemoDSS Unable to create an event handle\n");
2735  return ;
2736  }
2737  System_printf("Debug: MMWDemoDSS create event handle succeeded\n");
2738 
2739  /************************************************************************
2740  * mmwave library initialization
2741  ************************************************************************/
2742 
2743  /* Populate the init configuration for mmwave library: */
2744  initCfg.domain = MMWave_Domain_DSS;
2745  initCfg.socHandle = gMmwDssMCB.socHandle;
2746  initCfg.eventFxn = MmwDemo_dssMmwaveEventCallbackFxn;
2747  initCfg.linkCRCCfg.useCRCDriver = 1U;
2748  initCfg.linkCRCCfg.crcChannel = CRC_Channel_CH1;
2749  initCfg.cfgMode = MMWave_ConfigurationMode_FULL;
2750  initCfg.executionMode = MMWave_ExecutionMode_COOPERATIVE;
2751  initCfg.cooperativeModeCfg.cfgFxn = MmwDemo_dssMmwaveConfigCallbackFxn;
2752  initCfg.cooperativeModeCfg.startFxn = MmwDemo_dssMmwaveStartCallbackFxn;
2753  initCfg.cooperativeModeCfg.stopFxn = MmwDemo_dssMmwaveStopCallbackFxn;
2754  initCfg.cooperativeModeCfg.openFxn = MmwDemo_dssMmwaveOpenCallbackFxn;
2755  initCfg.cooperativeModeCfg.closeFxn = MmwDemo_dssMmwaveCloseCallbackFxn;
2756 
2757  /* Initialize and setup the mmWave Control module */
2758  gMmwDssMCB.ctrlHandle = MMWave_init (&initCfg, &errCode);
2759  if (gMmwDssMCB.ctrlHandle == NULL)
2760  {
2761  /* Error: Unable to initialize the mmWave control module */
2762  System_printf ("Error: MMWDemoDSS mmWave Control Initialization failed [Error code %d]\n", errCode);
2763  return;
2764  }
2765  System_printf ("Debug: MMWDemoDSS mmWave Control Initialization succeeded\n");
2766 
2767  /******************************************************************************
2768  * TEST: Synchronization
2769  * - The synchronization API always needs to be invoked.
2770  ******************************************************************************/
2771  while (1)
2772  {
2773  int32_t syncStatus;
2774 
2775  /* Get the synchronization status: */
2776  syncStatus = MMWave_sync (gMmwDssMCB.ctrlHandle , &errCode);
2777  if (syncStatus < 0)
2778  {
2779  /* Error: Unable to synchronize the mmWave control module */
2780  System_printf ("Error: MMWDemoDSS mmWave Control Synchronization failed [Error code %d]\n", errCode);
2781  return;
2782  }
2783  if (syncStatus == 1)
2784  {
2785  /* Synchronization acheived: */
2786  break;
2787  }
2788  /* Sleep and poll again: */
2789  Task_sleep(1);
2790  }
2791 
2792  /* Send the DSS to MSS signalling ISR payload address to the DSS. Note this
2793  should be done after both sides mailboxes have been opened, and because
2794  MMWave_sync above is a good one to check for synchronization, this is a good place */
2795  message.type = MMWDEMO_DSS2MSS_ISR_INFO_ADDRESS;
2796  message.body.dss2mssISRinfoAddress = (uint32_t) &gHSRAM.dss2MssIsrInfo;
2797  MmwDemo_mboxWrite(&message);
2798 
2799  /*****************************************************************************
2800  * Launch the mmWave control execution task
2801  * - This should have a higher priority than any other task which uses the
2802  * mmWave control API
2803  *****************************************************************************/
2804  Task_Params_init(&taskParams);
2805  taskParams.priority = 6;
2806  taskParams.stackSize = 4*1024;
2807  Task_create(MmwDemo_dssMMWaveCtrlTask, &taskParams, NULL);
2808 
2809  /*****************************************************************************
2810  * Data path Startup
2811  *****************************************************************************/
2812  if ((errCode = MmwDemo_dssDataPathInit()) < 0 )
2813  {
2814  System_printf ("Error: MMWDemoDSS Data Path init failed with Error[%d]\n",errCode);
2815  return;
2816  }
2817  System_printf ("Debug: MMWDemoDSS Data Path init succeeded\n");
2818  gMmwDssMCB.state = MmwDemo_DSS_STATE_INIT;
2819 
2820  /* Start data path task */
2821  Task_Params_init(&taskParams);
2822  taskParams.priority = 5;
2823  taskParams.stackSize = 4*1024;
2824  Task_create(MmwDemo_dssDataPathTask, &taskParams, NULL);
2825 
2826  System_printf("Debug: MMWDemoDSS initTask exit\n");
2827  return;
2828 }
